The paper discusses a framework for hyperparameter optimization in machine learning, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The framework is designed to be adaptable to any desired machine learning code, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The use of a bayesian optimizer also suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE), and the framework's adaptability could also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) applications.
